The defendant Ashley Vasquez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Ashley Vasquez is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

Filed by District Attorney Jane Kohlwey

Defendant Ashley Vasquez in court, in custody with attorney Adam Raabe.  Christine M. Genda appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Cases called: 11CM483, 14CF182, 14CF235, 15CF363.  In 15CF363 initial appearance was held.  Reading waived of complaint.   In 14CF182, 14CF235, & 15CF363  Waiver of Preliminary Hearing filed. Court found probable cause, bound defendant over. 14CF182, and 15CF363 Information filed.  Reading waived. Rights/Elements.  Defendant pled no contest to Ct. 1 of 15CF363 with enhancer dismissed, no contest to Ct. 1 of 14CF182.  Court found guilty.  Judgment was entered.  In 14CF182 Court dismissed Cts. 2,3, and 4. Court withheld sentencing placed defendant on probation for 3 years.  Conditions of probation include: $518.00 costs to be paid in the first two years of probation, submit DNA sample, AODA and comply,  psychological evaluation and comply, absolute sobriety.  In 15CF363 Court dismissed enhancer on Ct.1 and Ct. 2 dismissed.  Court withheld sentencing placed defendant on probation for 3 years.  Conditions of probation include:  90 days jail with Huber for work release.  $518.00 costs, submit DNA sample, AODA and comply,  psychological evaluation and comply, and absolute sobriety.  14CF235 Dismissed.  11CM483  Court withheld sentencing placed defendant on probation for 3 years concurrent to 15CF363, and 14CF182.  $543.00 costs.  Jail start on 10/16/15 at 7:00 pm.
